  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The model predicts absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all 13 credibility factors. Seven factors are formally assessed; six are flagged as epistemic gaps. All assessed factors achieve required levels under the Minimal profile review. Intended use scope is described in the bound Requirement and Claim nodes; the structured Context of Use object is not separately linked under this profile.",
